node.text: How about the festivals this summer? Let’s see some shots with #summerofdoomdays
Anyone make it to our Still Avoiding Tomorrow tour earlier in the year? Let’s see some of your best photos. Use #stillavoidingtomorrowtour and send our way.
“Oblivion” was the first video we made with @austinpshowem that we were not in at all. Here we chat with @vevo about how that worked (link in Story).

It felt totally right to end our decade touring our club nights round the UK. We had the best time with everyone who came along. 
Please send us your photos + tag them #DoomDaysClubNights 💙

Don’t forget to get out and vote today everyone. 
This country and everybody in it doesn’t deserve any more years of Boris Johnson’s bullshit. 
Imagine having a government that actually had respect for its population, the NHS, the environment and the truth. 👊🏼 #GE2019

I sat down with @austinpshowem for @vevo’s“Music Video Review” to have a look back at a bunch of our videos. The first one up is “Flaws” — the first video we worked on with Austin and the first we made outside the UK!  And there’s more to come. (Link in Story to watch.)

Last night of our #DoomDaysClubNights tour + last our gig of the DECADE, thank you so much to everyone tonight &everyone who’s come to our gigs this year for being fucking amazing. We’ll see you in future.

One of the highlights of our year was recording this ReOrchestrated version of “Million Pieces” with The London Chamber Orchestra for @amazonmusicuk at the iconic Abbey Road Studios. We’re so happy to have it out on “DOOM DAYS, THIS GOT OUT OF HAND”. Thanks so much for making it possible @amazonmusic

Pyramids in Portsmouth was so much fun last night... you would never have known it was a leisure centre on a Sunday night. Here are a load of photos by the brilliant @crookedcynics - so scroll ➡️ for more. Been bloody loving this whole tour and am sad it’s the last one tonight! Thanks to everyone who’s come along so far. #DoomDaysClubNights
TORQUAY WAS GOOD EH 💗 #DoomDaysClubNights
This is what the club nights were for. Thanks for getting sweaty and rowdy Torquay. #DoomDaysClubNights
Us and the Chaos Planet lot had a wicked time in Llandudno last night. Thank you! #DoomDaysClubNights 📸: @crookedcynics
Our expanded album “DOOM DAYS, THIS GOT OUT OF HAND Edition” is out now. Featuring new, previously unreleased & ReOrchestrated songs.
